        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <head>Municipal Council of Bolton</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Borough of Bolton, County of Lancaster,
                                England</hi>
                    </placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-10">May 10, 1865</date>.]</dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Copy of resolution of the council of the said borough,
                            unanimously passed at a meeting thereof, held on the</hi> 10<hi rend="italic">th day of May</hi>, 1865.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this council regards with intense
                        horror and detestation the diabolical assassination of President Lincoln,
                        the twice elected Chief Magistrate of the United States; and hereby records
                        its heartfelt sympathy with his widow and countrymen, in their mourning for
                        his loss and untimely end, hoping that their sorrow may speedily be assuaged
                        by the return of national peace and prosperity.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
